      LICENSE[0]=GPL
           SHORT="KNemo - the KDE Network Monitor"
cat << EOF
KNemo displays for every network interface an icon in the systray.
Tooltips and an info dialog provide further information about the
interface. Passive popups inform about interface changes. A traffic
plotter is also integrated. KNemo polls the network interface status
every second using the ifconfig, route and iwconfig tools. 

IMPORTANT: KNemo has to be started using KDE Control
Center/Internet & Network/Network Monitor. To start KNemo: Go to the
KDE Control Center / Internet & Networking / open the KNemo
configuration dialog (Network Monitor). There is an option at the
top of the dialog saying something like "Use KNemo to monitor your
interfaces". Activate it and KNemo should start with KDE.
EOF
